WEBVTT

00:15.917 --> 00:17.917
[razor scraping]

00:21.291 --> 00:23.166
[scraping continues]

00:24.542 --> 00:26.417
[clanking]

00:31.583 --> 00:33.625
[scraping]

00:44.542 --> 00:46.375
[birds chirping]

00:52.250 --> 00:54.375
[dull roar of traffic outside]

01:25.750 --> 01:27.750
[exhales heavily]

01:46.417 --> 01:47.792
[funeral director]
Mourners are arriving, sir.

01:47.875 --> 01:50.625
Fine. Let's begin.

02:01.750 --> 02:03.792
I want you...

02:05.792 --> 02:07.917
..to kill me.

02:13.125 --> 02:15.208
[woman]
Hello, Directory Enquiries?

02:15.291 --> 02:17.542
Yes, I'd like a number for
an organization, please.

02:17.625 --> 02:21.625
It's called the... the Voluntary
Euthanasia Society.

02:21.709 --> 02:24.083
I'm sorry,
you'll have to speak up.

02:24.166 --> 02:28.208
The Voluntary
Euthanasia Society.

02:28.291 --> 02:30.208
[man] I'm sorry, Mr. Melrose,
we can't help.

02:30.291 --> 02:33.041
- We're a campaign group.
It's about changing the law.
- Really?

02:33.125 --> 02:37.458
But I mean Voluntary Euthanasia,
it sounds so...hopeful.

02:37.542 --> 02:39.166
[woman] Directory Enquiries,
how can I help you?

02:39.250 --> 02:42.583
Er...yes, I'd like an
international number, please,
Switzerland.

02:42.667 --> 02:43.959
Dignitas.

02:44.041 --> 02:48.083
- And what kind of
organization are they?
-  [knocking]

02:48.166 --> 02:51.583
- What...what does it do?
-  Well, they...

02:51.667 --> 02:52.792
I'll spell it for you.

02:52.875 --> 02:54.250
Suicide stems from a disease:

02:54.333 --> 02:56.166
a disease
we now call depression.

02:56.250 --> 02:58.750
And that's what
we should be treating.

02:58.834 --> 03:01.750
She can't move
or speak or control herself.

03:01.834 --> 03:05.583
Depression isn't a disease, it's
an entirely reasonable response.

03:05.667 --> 03:09.542
Quite frankly, it's cheerfulness
that would take some explaining.

03:09.625 --> 03:12.208
When people are depressed
we give them anti-depressants.

03:12.291 --> 03:13.417
She's on them!

03:13.500 --> 03:16.750
They gave a certain enthusiasm
for her loathing of life.

03:16.834 --> 03:18.750
That's when
she asked me to kill her.

03:18.834 --> 03:20.709
Do you know?
It can be a great privilege
to work with the dying.

03:20.792 --> 03:24.834
I don't think she's gonna start
working with the dying, do you?

03:24.917 --> 03:26.625
And if you mean
it's your  great privilege,

03:26.709 --> 03:29.041
it's her  quality of life
I'm concerned with.

03:36.041 --> 03:38.792
I...I want...

03:38.875 --> 03:40.917
Swiss-land.

03:41.875 --> 03:43.125
That's what we're looking into.

03:43.208 --> 03:45.959
[door opens and closes]

03:46.041 --> 03:48.125
Doctor Fenelon is here.

03:48.208 --> 03:50.834
Do you remember,
our family doctor?

03:50.917 --> 03:53.875
Hello, Eleanor.

03:53.959 --> 03:58.000
So, I'm going to take a look
at you and ask a few questions.

04:01.291 --> 04:04.291
Please...don't tell him...

04:06.583 --> 04:08.583
..that my mother was...

04:10.709 --> 04:11.959
..a duchess.

04:13.125 --> 04:15.250
I won't breathe a word.

04:16.458 --> 04:19.625
[Mary] "I can hardly move.
I am bedridden and incontinent

04:19.709 --> 04:22.583
and feel uninterrupted anguish
at my own uselessness.

04:24.375 --> 04:26.166
There is no prospect
of improvement

04:26.250 --> 04:28.500
and I can already feel
my faculties betraying me.

04:28.583 --> 04:32.875
I do not look on death
with fear, but with longing.

04:32.959 --> 04:36.834
Please help me to escape the
daily torture of my existence.

04:38.834 --> 04:40.166
Yours sincerely."

04:43.250 --> 04:45.333
Do you think that's fair?

04:49.875 --> 04:51.750
Is that a fair description?

04:53.417 --> 04:55.417
Yes.

04:56.041 --> 04:58.917
Do you want to sign it?

05:03.834 --> 05:05.583
Sign.

05:16.125 --> 05:18.500
Thank you so much
for doing all of this.

05:18.583 --> 05:20.542
It's really not your
responsibility anymore.

05:22.834 --> 05:24.667
You're welcome.

05:27.834 --> 05:30.542
- So...
- An orphan at last!

05:30.625 --> 05:32.291
It's what I always dreamed of.

05:32.375 --> 05:34.458
After all this time,
I feel complete.

05:34.542 --> 05:38.041
[chuckles]
I hope that's not your speech.

05:38.125 --> 05:40.500
Ah, well, my speech...

05:40.583 --> 05:42.750
Because it is printed
in the order of service.

05:42.834 --> 05:45.709
I know.

05:45.792 --> 05:48.709
- I can't do that for you.
- I wouldn't ask you to.

05:48.792 --> 05:50.417
So you've written one?

05:50.500 --> 05:52.333
I thought it'd probably
be better to improvise,

05:52.417 --> 05:54.125
speak from the heart.

05:54.208 --> 05:56.625
- Is that a good idea?
- With my heart?

05:56.709 --> 05:59.041
There'll probably be
a stampede for the exit.

05:59.125 --> 06:00.792
Surprised to see me?

06:00.875 --> 06:03.750
I've become rather
a memorial creeper.

06:03.834 --> 06:05.625
One's bound to at my age.

06:05.709 --> 06:07.250
It's no use sitting at home,

06:07.333 --> 06:09.417
guffawing over the mistakes
of ignorant obituarists.

06:09.500 --> 06:13.125
Thank you. No, one has
to celebrate the life!

06:13.208 --> 06:15.417
"There goes the school tart.

06:15.500 --> 06:18.291
They say he had a good war,
but I know better!"

06:18.375 --> 06:22.792
[chuckles] Of course I'm not
saying it's not all very moving.

06:22.875 --> 06:26.166
- [indistinct chatter]
- Thinly attended.

06:26.250 --> 06:28.333
Are those your mother's
religious friends?

06:28.417 --> 06:31.375
What color would you call that?
Aubergine?

06:31.458 --> 06:32.291
Forgive me, Nicholas,
I really must talk to--

06:32.375 --> 06:34.125
Try not to be bitter
about the money.

06:34.208 --> 06:35.458
One or two of my friends

06:35.542 --> 06:38.125
who've made a mess
of that side of things

06:38.208 --> 06:40.959
have ended up dying
in National Health wards,

06:41.041 --> 06:43.041
and I must say
I've been very impressed

06:43.125 --> 06:46.083
by the humanity of
the mainly foreign staff.

06:46.166 --> 06:48.291
Mind you, what else
is there to do with money,

06:48.375 --> 06:50.792
but spend it when you have it
and be bitter when you don't?

06:50.875 --> 06:55.917
I suppose what I'm saying is -
do be bitter about the money.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.041
After all, what is it now,

06:58.125 --> 07:00.041
six generations
with every single descendant

07:00.125 --> 07:02.125
essentially idle?

07:02.208 --> 07:04.625
It must be rather thrilling
for you and your children,

07:04.709 --> 07:07.750
after such a long exemption
from competition,

07:07.834 --> 07:10.333
- to get really stuck in!
- Goodbye, Nicholas.

07:10.417 --> 07:14.041
And you mustn't feel guilty
about feeling pleased.

07:16.375 --> 07:18.542
If ever there was
a merciful release,

07:18.625 --> 07:21.208
it was in the case of
your poor mother.

07:29.333 --> 07:33.208
Eleanor, it's time to go.

07:33.917 --> 07:36.208
The flight leaves at three.

07:36.792 --> 07:39.125
Do...nothing. Noth...

07:41.458 --> 07:43.583
[Mary] What was that?

07:44.333 --> 07:47.500
Do...nothing.
No go.

07:47.583 --> 07:49.792
You mean...
you've changed your mind?

07:52.959 --> 07:54.792
No...Swiss-land.

08:00.667 --> 08:03.041
I'm entitled to feel a little
ambiguous about this,

08:03.125 --> 08:04.000
don't you think?

08:04.083 --> 08:05.959
I mean, she asked me
to organize this,

08:06.041 --> 08:08.709
- the doctors,
the letter of consent--
- I know.

08:08.792 --> 08:12.417
..manipulated me, turned her
death into this passion project,
and now she changes her mind.

08:12.500 --> 08:15.375
She's frightened. She
doesn't want to do it herself.

08:15.458 --> 08:17.208
She wants
someone else to do it for her.

08:17.291 --> 08:18.750
Oh, believe me,
I'm sorely tempted.

08:18.834 --> 08:22.750
Why isn't there a bar in this
place? It would make a fortune.

08:22.834 --> 08:25.792
- Come... Come and talk to her.
- What's the point?

08:25.875 --> 08:29.834
If she ever had anything
meaningful to say to me,
it's too late now.

08:29.917 --> 08:31.875
♪ ♪

08:37.166 --> 08:39.500
[clinking]

08:40.291 --> 08:42.375
[bottles clinking]

08:42.917 --> 08:44.667
[keys clatter]

08:45.166 --> 08:47.875
[rustling]

09:00.000 --> 09:01.834
[train rattles past]

09:04.333 --> 09:06.208
Were you thinking about Eleanor?

09:09.375 --> 09:12.875
Annette.
We met in France, remember?

09:12.959 --> 09:16.250
Yes. I hope you're enjoying
my family home.

09:16.333 --> 09:18.959
Oh, we are!

09:19.041 --> 09:20.375
Seamus sends his love.

09:20.458 --> 09:23.208
- Oh, he's in your
old bedroom now!
- Oh.

09:23.291 --> 09:26.792
He really wanted to be here
but he's still writing his book.

09:27.458 --> 09:30.250
How are you taking all this?

09:31.291 --> 09:32.458
I was thinking how life
is just the history

09:32.542 --> 09:35.041
of things
we pay attention to.

09:35.125 --> 09:37.041
The rest is just packaging.

09:39.792 --> 09:45.166
Maya Angelou says the
meaning of life is the impact

09:45.250 --> 09:49.291
we have on other people, whether
we make them feel good or not.

09:51.083 --> 09:54.542
Eleanor always made
people feel good.

09:54.625 --> 09:57.250
- I might put that in my speech.
- You should!

09:57.750 --> 09:59.375
My gift to you.

10:01.458 --> 10:02.625
I tell you who loves
Maya Angelou,

10:02.709 --> 10:05.500
is that old man over there,
with the stick.

10:05.583 --> 10:07.709
Do tell him.
His name's Nick.

10:08.417 --> 10:10.458
Will do!

10:12.291 --> 10:14.792
Hello! You must be Nick.

10:14.875 --> 10:17.959
Patrick, of all the days
to have a funeral!

10:18.041 --> 10:19.625
It's Prince Charles' wedding!

10:19.709 --> 10:22.333
Well, feel free to pop down
with your cardboard periscope

10:22.417 --> 10:25.333
and a plastic Union Jack if you
think it'd be more entertaining.

10:25.417 --> 10:28.917
- [sighs]
- Alright?

10:31.291 --> 10:32.542
Lovely venue.

10:32.625 --> 10:34.041
Yes, I'm thinking of getting
cremated here myself.

10:34.125 --> 10:37.959
- Well, no need to rush.
- I was going to wait
until I die.

10:38.041 --> 10:39.917
Hm. How are you bearing up?

10:41.041 --> 10:42.542
Weirdly elated.

10:42.625 --> 10:45.250
I think my mother's death
is the best thing to have
happened to me since,

10:45.333 --> 10:47.041
well, my father's death.

10:47.125 --> 10:48.959
I'm sure it's a little more
complicated than that.

10:49.041 --> 10:51.041
- You're the psychiatrist.
- Psychotherapist.

10:51.125 --> 10:52.208
Oh, whatever.

10:52.291 --> 10:54.166
[Nicholas]
What utter, utter nonsense.

10:54.250 --> 10:57.083
- Stand by the furnace...
- Oh, Christ, Nicholas Pratt.

10:57.166 --> 10:58.417
..these words.
"Goodbye, old thing.

10:58.500 --> 11:01.500
One of us was bound to die first
and I'm delighted it was you!"

11:01.583 --> 11:03.166
That's my spiritual practice

11:03.250 --> 11:05.542
and you're welcome to
put it in your hilarious
"spiritual tool box".

11:05.625 --> 11:08.458
Isn't he hysterical? [chuckles]

11:08.542 --> 11:12.291
What he doesn't realize is that
we live in a loving universe,

11:12.375 --> 11:15.250
and it loves you too, Nick!

11:15.333 --> 11:16.750
My dear, I never thought
I'd be so pleased to see you!

11:16.834 --> 11:19.291
Nicholas, who are
these peculiar people?

11:19.375 --> 11:22.250
And why are they here?

11:22.333 --> 11:24.208
Zealots, Moonies, witch doctors.

11:24.291 --> 11:26.417
Avoid eye contact,
stick close to me

11:26.500 --> 11:27.250
and we may live
to tell the tale.

11:27.333 --> 11:30.333
Well, who is he?

11:30.417 --> 11:31.250
He wouldn't be anybody

11:31.333 --> 11:33.417
if he wasn't my
daughter's psychoanalyst.

11:33.500 --> 11:36.250
As it is, he's a fiend!

11:42.583 --> 11:43.542
We can start
when you're ready, sir.

11:43.625 --> 11:46.875
- Ten minutes.
- Ten minutes?

11:46.959 --> 11:48.208
Well, there are people
still arriving!

11:48.291 --> 11:49.709
[sighs]

11:49.792 --> 11:52.625
Just in time.
We're about to kick off,

11:52.709 --> 11:55.083
if that's the er...
phrase I'm looking for.

11:55.166 --> 11:57.959
Hm. It's not.

11:58.041 --> 12:01.000
- It's been a long time.
- Almost a year.

12:02.542 --> 12:03.333
Is it true you've given up
drinking again?

12:03.417 --> 12:06.542
Yes, that's all over.

12:06.625 --> 12:08.291
Congratulations.

12:08.375 --> 12:09.417
It must be hard just now.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.458
Not at all.
A crisis demands a hero.

12:11.542 --> 12:13.333
The ambush happens
when things are going well.

12:13.417 --> 12:15.500
- Or so I'm told.
- Still not given up irony,
then?

12:15.583 --> 12:17.959
Hardest addiction of all.

12:18.041 --> 12:20.792
Forget heroin, that need
to mean two things at once...

12:20.875 --> 12:24.041
I'm having enough trouble
wearing nicotine patches

12:24.125 --> 12:25.583
and smoking at the same time.

12:25.667 --> 12:28.250
Don't take my irony,
leave me with a little sarcasm!

12:28.333 --> 12:30.291
Sarcasm doesn't count.
That only means one thing.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.458
Quality freak.

12:34.166 --> 12:37.166
We'd better go inside.
Apparently the corpses
are piling up.

12:37.250 --> 12:38.208
Very exciting.
Who's on the bill?

12:38.291 --> 12:39.709
I've no idea.

12:39.792 --> 12:43.458
- Mary's organized it.
- Adorable.

12:43.542 --> 12:46.625
More like a mother
than your own mother, really.

12:46.709 --> 12:48.750
She was,
until she had her own children

12:48.834 --> 12:49.959
and that rather blew my cover.

12:52.583 --> 12:54.000
Still, real or not real,

12:54.083 --> 12:56.792
I have to burn the remains of
the only mother I'll ever have.

12:58.250 --> 13:01.917
It's good to see you again.
I wasn't sure I would.

13:08.291 --> 13:10.250
♪ ♪

13:13.458 --> 13:15.291
[Julia sighs]

13:15.959 --> 13:17.625
[inhales]

13:17.709 --> 13:19.458
[exhales heavily]

13:19.542 --> 13:21.542
[siren wails]

13:23.542 --> 13:25.750
You're not really
gonna live here, are you?

13:28.417 --> 13:32.041
I'm trying to think of it
as my bachelor pad.

13:32.125 --> 13:34.709
It's the kind of place
people come to kill themselves.

13:34.792 --> 13:37.875
Yes.
The thought had crossed my mind.

13:37.959 --> 13:40.125
Don't! Be serious.

13:41.458 --> 13:43.875
Christ, it's all so bleak!

13:46.667 --> 13:48.500
But, I'm sorry,

13:48.583 --> 13:51.208
squalor is not an aphrodisiac,
not at our age.

13:51.291 --> 13:53.083
I can't come here again.

13:56.959 --> 13:59.875
[gulps]
No, I don't think you should.

14:23.834 --> 14:27.583
[indistinct conversation
from other room]

14:27.667 --> 14:29.417
- [book thuds]
- [conversation continues]

14:29.500 --> 14:31.417
[clattering]

14:31.500 --> 14:34.458
[Mary] Robert?
What are you doing in there?

14:36.417 --> 14:39.166
Hello. Ssh-ssh.

14:39.959 --> 14:43.458
I didn't hear you. Come here.

14:43.542 --> 14:45.625
[door creaks]

14:45.709 --> 14:47.959
- What's going on?
- I'm picking up a few things.

14:48.041 --> 14:49.250
How are you?

14:49.333 --> 14:50.875
Robert, will you take Thomas
upstairs, please?

14:50.959 --> 14:53.625
But we haven't seen each other.
Robert, how are you?
Are you well?

14:53.709 --> 14:56.458
How's school?
Where is Thomas?

14:56.542 --> 14:58.625
Now, please.

15:00.709 --> 15:03.083
I'll come up and say goodbye.

15:10.041 --> 15:13.208
Just a few bits and bobs,
if that's alright. You know.

15:13.291 --> 15:18.291
Just a few family heirlooms to
brighten up the bachelor pad...

15:18.375 --> 15:20.917
Fine, take what you want. And
you can go back to your flat.

15:21.000 --> 15:22.333
Pass out there.

15:22.417 --> 15:24.709
But I don't want the children
to see you in this state.

15:24.792 --> 15:26.959
[smashing and clattering]

15:28.834 --> 15:30.792
Oops!

15:32.417 --> 15:35.583
Don't worry about the lamp,
I'll buy you a new bloody lamp.

15:35.667 --> 15:38.417
- [groans]
- Leave it and go home!

15:38.500 --> 15:39.667
Home!

15:39.750 --> 15:42.458
How sweet of you
to think of it as my home!

15:42.542 --> 15:44.417
I am not in the happy position
of having a home.

15:44.500 --> 15:47.500
[Mary] Christ, this is hell!
This is like being in hell!

15:47.583 --> 15:53.166
You - you of all people,
should know this is intolerable!

15:53.250 --> 15:55.917
You know?
"The service is intolerable,
the noise is intolerable."

15:56.000 --> 15:59.333
Well, this...
this is fucking intolerable!

16:00.542 --> 16:03.542
I am not Eleanor
and I will not stand by

16:03.625 --> 16:06.709
and watch this disgusting,
pitiful spectacle of you

16:06.792 --> 16:09.291
destroying yourself.

16:09.375 --> 16:12.458
And I certainly won't let
the boys watch it, either.

16:12.542 --> 16:14.083
It's too much.

16:14.959 --> 16:17.583
And it's gone on for too long.

16:18.792 --> 16:23.208
If you really are determined
to drink yourself to death,

16:23.291 --> 16:26.375
now you have a flat
to go and do it in.

16:31.583 --> 16:33.250
[door slams]

16:33.709 --> 16:36.458
[key in lock]

16:40.417 --> 16:42.834
[bottles clinking]

16:44.750 --> 16:46.709
[clinking]

16:50.667 --> 16:53.458
♪ ominous music ♪

17:12.542 --> 17:14.291
[Robert] Daddy?

17:38.750 --> 17:40.709
[grunts]

17:49.917 --> 17:51.834
[groans and shivers]

17:57.917 --> 17:59.959
[groans]

18:00.333 --> 18:01.417
[mumbles]

18:05.834 --> 18:08.625
- [grunts]
- [rustling]

18:10.917 --> 18:12.917
[groans]

18:13.000 --> 18:13.959
[female doctor] You're
undergoing delirium tremens.

18:14.041 --> 18:17.000
Do you know what that is,
Mr. Melrose?

18:17.083 --> 18:18.834
It...rings a bell.

18:18.917 --> 18:20.667
Then you'll know what to expect.

18:20.750 --> 18:22.500
Shaking, sweating.

18:22.583 --> 18:23.875
There may be
some hallucinations.

18:23.959 --> 18:25.166
We'll get you something
to stabilize your heart,

18:25.250 --> 18:27.667
- stop you having seizures.
- [groans]

18:27.750 --> 18:30.875
- I'm going to die.
- You are not going to die.

18:30.959 --> 18:33.375
I don't mind. I want to die.

18:34.542 --> 18:36.667
I want to die, I want to die.

18:37.125 --> 18:39.000
I want to die.

18:39.083 --> 18:41.333
♪ ominous music ♪

18:42.750 --> 18:44.875
[breathes erratically]

19:12.000 --> 19:15.709
♪ When I die I want you to dress
me in straight-lace shoes ♪

19:16.792 --> 19:20.792
♪ A box-back coat
and a Stetson hat ♪

19:20.875 --> 19:25.000
♪ Put a twenty-dollar gold
piece
on my watch chain ♪

19:25.083 --> 19:29.542
Oh, Christ.
It's the Spiritual Tool Box.

19:29.625 --> 19:30.917
[song fades]

19:31.000 --> 19:34.709
What a great choice for Eleanor.

19:34.792 --> 19:39.875
And a fitting reminder, too, of
her incredibly strong connection

19:39.959 --> 19:42.709
with the
African-American people.

19:42.792 --> 19:45.041
All of you will have known
Eleanor here today

19:45.125 --> 19:49.959
and...if my Eleanor...
is not yours

19:50.041 --> 19:53.834
then, all I can say is...

19:55.792 --> 19:57.834
..let her in.

19:58.583 --> 20:01.041
- Let her in.
- [sniggering]

20:01.125 --> 20:03.500
I first met Eleanor
when a group of us

20:03.583 --> 20:05.250
from the Dublin Women's
Healing Drum Circle

20:05.333 --> 20:08.917
traveled down to her
wonderful house in Provence,

20:09.000 --> 20:11.667
which many of you know well.

20:13.125 --> 20:15.875
When we arrived
we saw her sitting

20:15.959 --> 20:18.625
on the wall of the terrace,

20:18.709 --> 20:21.458
hands tucked under her thighs,

20:21.542 --> 20:26.125
looking for all the world
like a lonely young child,

20:26.208 --> 20:29.500
dreaming of the future.

20:29.583 --> 20:33.875
Soon she had flung wide
her arms to welcome us,

20:33.959 --> 20:36.250
but I never forgot

20:36.333 --> 20:39.375
that first impression of
her child-like innocence...

20:41.166 --> 20:42.375
♪ somber music ♪

21:20.500 --> 21:23.375
[Eleanor] I can never forget
he's David's son.

21:25.750 --> 21:27.291
Does he remind you of him?

21:27.375 --> 21:32.500
In flashes...
when he's angry or sarcastic.

21:33.875 --> 21:35.208
Which thankfully
is less often now.

21:35.291 --> 21:38.208
- [Patrick calls out]
- Hm.

21:39.959 --> 21:43.125
Does he talk to you about him?

21:43.208 --> 21:46.542
I don't think his father haunts
him the way he once did.

21:47.792 --> 21:49.625
"Haunts".

21:52.291 --> 21:54.250
- [Robert cries out]
[Patrick] I'm gonna catch you.

21:56.709 --> 21:58.834
May I show you something,
in private?

22:00.959 --> 22:01.875
I get an awful lot of letters,

22:01.959 --> 22:04.375
usually people asking
for a helping hand.

22:04.458 --> 22:08.000
And I give it if I can, but...
this is something different.

22:08.709 --> 22:11.083
She stayed here as a child.

22:13.041 --> 22:16.125
She seems...deeply damaged.

22:16.208 --> 22:17.083
Yes.

22:17.166 --> 22:20.625
I mean, clearly
she's a very unhappy woman -

22:20.709 --> 22:22.625
the alcohol, the depression.

22:22.709 --> 22:24.208
But, honestly,
to lay this at my door.

22:24.291 --> 22:26.125
- Do you remember her?
- Of course!

22:26.208 --> 22:28.083
The family were charming.

22:28.166 --> 22:31.750
She was a bright
and happy little girl.

22:31.834 --> 22:35.917
David could be harsh, but
the children were always safe.

22:36.000 --> 22:38.834
He was better with children,
playful even,

22:38.917 --> 22:40.417
as long as
they weren't too noisy.

22:40.500 --> 22:42.000
[exhales]

22:42.083 --> 22:42.917
[scoffs]

22:43.000 --> 22:46.917
All I know is the family
seemed very happy.

22:47.000 --> 22:49.333
They... They told me
they'd had a lovely time.

22:49.417 --> 22:52.959
She says your husband
interfered with her.

22:53.041 --> 22:55.417
But how could he?

22:55.500 --> 22:58.959
I mean, it was inconceivable -
literally, inconceivable.

22:59.041 --> 23:02.458
- No suspicions?
- No.

23:02.542 --> 23:04.625
No signs?

23:04.709 --> 23:06.500
None at all. And that's
what makes me so angry.

23:08.792 --> 23:10.834
"I forgive you."

23:10.917 --> 23:14.792
She forgives me for not
protecting her, but how could I?

23:14.875 --> 23:17.041
From what?

23:17.125 --> 23:20.583
I mean, this is behavior
I didn't even know existed.

23:22.709 --> 23:24.709
[Patrick] Here we go.
- [Robert laughs]

23:24.792 --> 23:26.667
You mustn't mention
a word of this.

23:26.750 --> 23:29.208
It will only unsettle him...

23:29.291 --> 23:33.542
all this talk of...
blame and forgiveness.

23:35.000 --> 23:38.041
I know what a tyrant
his father could be,

23:38.125 --> 23:40.333
but I did my best -

23:40.417 --> 23:44.375
my very, very best
to protect our son.

23:48.125 --> 23:50.208
Are you awake?

24:04.750 --> 24:08.250
The things...you told me,
when we met.

24:09.083 --> 24:11.959
About your father.

24:14.000 --> 24:18.000
- What's brought this on?
- We have to talk about them
again.

24:22.250 --> 24:25.000
Well, I don't think I have
anything further to add so...

24:25.083 --> 24:29.375
I think...
you should tell your mother.

24:29.458 --> 24:31.166
- [inhales sharply]
- I'm sorry, I know it's hard.

24:31.250 --> 24:33.375
I know you don't want to.

24:33.458 --> 24:35.709
- Well, why then?
- Because...

24:37.291 --> 24:40.250
She can't keep hiding.

24:45.291 --> 24:47.125
[Mary] "When I was a child

24:47.208 --> 24:50.166
I spake as a child.

24:51.125 --> 24:53.792
I understood as a child.

24:55.375 --> 24:59.417
When I became a man,
I put away childish things.

24:59.500 --> 25:03.709
For now
I see through a glass, darkly.

25:05.083 --> 25:09.750
But then, face to face,
now I know in part..."

25:09.834 --> 25:12.792
Christ, not this old chestnut.

25:12.875 --> 25:14.583
Who's on next?

25:14.667 --> 25:17.250
- Patrick.
- "..and now abideth faith,

25:17.333 --> 25:21.417
hope, love, these three.

25:21.500 --> 25:25.500
But the greatest of these...
is love.

25:27.166 --> 25:29.709
[exhales]

25:31.542 --> 25:32.625
[insects chirping]

25:35.000 --> 25:36.834
[Patrick] Lovely spot.

25:37.500 --> 25:39.583
[Eleanor] It is.

25:40.375 --> 25:43.542
- Mind if I join?
- Please.

25:43.625 --> 25:45.625
♪ ♪

25:51.083 --> 25:52.834
[Patrick exhales]

26:09.375 --> 26:11.333
I've been trying out different
combinations of words,

26:11.417 --> 26:16.333
and none of them are right,
so perhaps if I don't think too
much and just come out with it.

26:21.125 --> 26:23.875
When we were here...

26:23.959 --> 26:26.417
..when I was a child,
and we used to come here...

26:28.000 --> 26:29.792
and for some years afterwards...

26:32.583 --> 26:34.583
..Father used...

26:42.375 --> 26:44.375
..he used to rape me.

26:49.083 --> 26:49.834
Me too.

26:56.208 --> 26:57.959
Me too.

27:09.291 --> 27:11.959
[ragged breaths]

27:19.083 --> 27:22.041
Er... I...
I haven't prepared a speech.

27:24.125 --> 27:25.917
As you'll see.

27:26.250 --> 27:28.166
Erm...

27:35.125 --> 27:38.250
A lot has been said today
about my mother's innocence,

27:38.333 --> 27:41.291
and how child-like she...

27:47.333 --> 27:49.917
[exhales heavily]

27:50.000 --> 27:52.750
All I know is
that when I was a child...

27:58.375 --> 27:59.792
..when my father was...

28:14.333 --> 28:16.000
[tearfully] Why didn't she...

28:19.625 --> 28:21.375
Why... Why couldn't...
Why couldn't she...

28:21.458 --> 28:24.583
[breathing heavily]

28:24.667 --> 28:26.959
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, I can't...

28:27.041 --> 28:28.375
I can't do this...I can't!

28:28.458 --> 28:30.458
[shocked murmuring]

28:33.458 --> 28:35.250
[door opens and closes]

28:35.333 --> 28:38.166
♪ piano music ♪

28:50.583 --> 28:52.709
[cigarette lighter clicking]

28:55.250 --> 28:58.625
I swear, if I hear one
more person telling me
how innocent she was--

28:58.709 --> 29:00.166
She might not have been,

29:00.250 --> 29:02.959
- but even so
it's an emotional time--
- Please, Mary, no. No, no, no.

29:03.041 --> 29:05.375
Stop!
This is not grief or mourning.

29:05.458 --> 29:08.041
This is rage,
my heart is racing with it.

29:08.125 --> 29:10.417
She knew! She must have known.

29:10.500 --> 29:13.000
Surely she must have,
even subconsciously.

29:13.083 --> 29:14.250
She knew what he was like

29:14.333 --> 29:17.000
and yet she failed to do the one
thing she was obliged to do,

29:17.083 --> 29:19.667
to protect her son!

29:19.750 --> 29:22.959
Christ knows, I've been
a fucking useless father
and a useless husband.

29:23.041 --> 29:24.417
And I'm sorry, I'm so sorry.

29:24.500 --> 29:27.583
But if I thought someone
was gonna harm our children,
I would fight.

29:27.667 --> 29:31.667
Even I would do whatever it
takes because if you love
someone, you protect them.

29:31.750 --> 29:32.834
But my mother?

29:32.917 --> 29:35.834
Christ, no wonder
he stuck with her!

29:37.333 --> 29:41.333
All those children around and
a son thrown into the bargain.

29:42.583 --> 29:44.917
[tearfully] He couldn't believe
his fucking luck!

29:45.333 --> 29:47.500
[sniffles]

29:47.583 --> 29:52.250
Years and years and years of it,
doing whatever he wanted,

29:52.333 --> 29:54.208
whenever he wanted.

29:56.750 --> 29:58.667
Nobody should do that
to anybody else.

30:00.709 --> 30:02.500
No...

30:06.834 --> 30:09.125
Christ, Mary.

30:09.208 --> 30:10.500
[grunts]

30:10.583 --> 30:13.291
I thought I was getting better,
but I'm such a fucking mess.

30:13.375 --> 30:16.125
[exhales heavily]

30:23.625 --> 30:25.834
♪ somber music ♪

31:02.375 --> 31:05.625
[female doctor] How often
would you say you have
suicidal thoughts?

31:06.834 --> 31:08.542
When I was younger
it was all the time,

31:08.625 --> 31:11.041
I never questioned it.

31:11.125 --> 31:15.583
But then, when we had the boys
it was...more of a whisper.

31:16.166 --> 31:17.542
On a quiet coastal path,

31:17.625 --> 31:21.041
in the chemist...

31:24.959 --> 31:27.291
..driving on the motorway.

31:27.375 --> 31:29.125
[clock ticking]

31:30.875 --> 31:34.083
- And now?
- [exhales heavily]

31:36.875 --> 31:40.917
I look at the window
and wonder whether
this floor is high enough.

31:45.709 --> 31:48.500
Are you gonna be alright?

31:48.583 --> 31:50.792
[inhales] Let's find out.

31:56.417 --> 31:58.667
- Daddy!
- Thomas!

31:58.750 --> 32:01.333
Hah!

32:01.417 --> 32:02.667
Hello, how are you?
How's your other granny?

32:02.750 --> 32:05.875
- The same.
[Kettle] Patrick!

32:05.959 --> 32:09.458
After the disinheritance, it
would have been hypocritical
of me to go to the funeral.

32:09.542 --> 32:10.667
But the party's
a different matter.

32:10.750 --> 32:11.959
I want to support you.

32:12.041 --> 32:15.083
And, of course, it helps with it
being just around the corner.

32:15.166 --> 32:16.917
Patrick, what an unusual speech.
So eloquent.

32:17.000 --> 32:18.875
And how thrilling
to be introduced,

32:18.959 --> 32:22.333
at my advanced age,
to a new club.

32:22.417 --> 32:25.875
The Onslow Club!
I've never heard it mentioned...

32:25.959 --> 32:30.208
- Is this your eldest?
- Yes. Robert.

32:30.291 --> 32:32.834
What a pity David isn't here
to enjoy your sons.

32:32.917 --> 32:35.250
He would at least have ensured

32:35.333 --> 32:38.917
that they didn't spend the whole
day in front of the television.

32:39.000 --> 32:42.458
Ha! I vividly remember, when we
had once seen some children

32:42.542 --> 32:45.959
practically give birth
to a cathode ray tube,

32:46.041 --> 32:48.333
he said to me, "I dread to think

32:48.417 --> 32:51.458
what all that radiation is doing
to their little genitals."

32:51.542 --> 32:54.458
Robert, why don't you run ahead
and find your mother?

32:56.750 --> 32:58.000
How's your daughter, Nicholas?

32:59.125 --> 33:00.959
Well, I presume.

33:01.041 --> 33:03.083
We've not spoken for years.

33:04.834 --> 33:07.500
I can't help thinking
how much your father

33:07.583 --> 33:09.709
would have savored
this occasion.

33:09.792 --> 33:10.917
Whatever his drawbacks
as a parent,

33:11.000 --> 33:13.542
he never lost his sense
of humor.

33:13.625 --> 33:15.166
Easy not to lose
what you never had.

33:15.250 --> 33:17.458
Oh, I disagree. He saw
the funny side in everything.

33:17.542 --> 33:19.375
He only ever saw the funny side
of things that didn't have one.

33:19.458 --> 33:23.333
Cruelty and laughter have
always been close neighbors.

33:23.417 --> 33:25.125
Close without being incestuous.

33:25.208 --> 33:30.417
Your father had a rare
and precious disdain

33:30.500 --> 33:31.792
for the opinions
of most people--

33:31.875 --> 33:35.250
Nicholas, I understand
how much you must miss
my other amazing parent,

33:35.333 --> 33:36.834
- but if you'll forgive me...
- ..morality...a colossus.

33:36.917 --> 33:40.333
..I have to deal with the people
that have come here
to mourn my mother.

33:42.458 --> 33:43.375
Are you alright, there, Nick?

33:43.458 --> 33:46.375
Did you get yourself
in a bit of a muddle?

33:46.458 --> 33:49.041
[grunts] Do not call me Nick!

33:49.125 --> 33:50.166
[chatter]

33:55.625 --> 33:57.625
Excuse me.

33:57.709 --> 33:58.667
I can't breathe.

33:58.750 --> 34:00.208
It feels like someone's
squeezing my throat.

34:00.291 --> 34:04.542
To see that... to see
that ghoul Nicholas Pratt,

34:04.625 --> 34:05.792
my father's representative
on earth, touching Robert.

34:05.875 --> 34:07.959
I can't be in the same room.

34:08.041 --> 34:09.542
- Wine or champagne?
- Oh, God!

34:09.625 --> 34:11.583
- He means no, thank you.
- Maybe later.

34:11.667 --> 34:13.625
Very much later.
Oh, have some water.

34:13.709 --> 34:14.709
Oh, Christ. I know her.

34:14.792 --> 34:17.500
It's Amitriptyline.
What the fuck is she doing here?

34:17.583 --> 34:18.917
Who?

34:19.000 --> 34:20.792
No. No, no, no.
I need to get some fresh air.

34:20.875 --> 34:23.458
I'm going to go for
a walk round the block.

34:23.542 --> 34:25.542
♪ ♪

34:25.625 --> 34:27.375
[wings fluttering]

34:36.709 --> 34:38.875
[panting]

34:43.917 --> 34:45.917
[breathing slows]

34:46.041 --> 34:48.000
[inhales]

34:48.083 --> 34:48.250
[exhales]

34:50.291 --> 34:56.834
The thing is...
I absolutely loathe my children.

34:56.917 --> 34:59.000
They're monsters,
they're complete horrors.

35:00.041 --> 35:03.667
And, of course,
I've played my part.

35:03.750 --> 35:06.875
I lay in bed for ten months,
I didn't utter a single syllable

35:06.959 --> 35:07.959
And when I did start
I couldn't stop

35:08.041 --> 35:10.959
because it had
all just piled up.

35:16.625 --> 35:19.583
[woman] I woke up next
morning in the guest room

35:19.667 --> 35:23.291
and there was excrement,
human excrement,

35:23.375 --> 35:27.458
smeared all over the
hand-painted wallpaper.

35:29.792 --> 35:33.208
And it took me a while
to realize that it was mine.

35:36.834 --> 35:39.542
I think we need
to be aware of the alcoholic

35:39.625 --> 35:41.542
behind the alcohol.

35:41.625 --> 35:44.041
You can take the brandy
out of the fruitcake,

35:44.125 --> 35:47.125
but you've still got
the fruitcake.

35:48.959 --> 35:50.208
- I don't think you can.
- What?

35:50.291 --> 35:54.250
Take the brandy
out of the fruitcake.

35:54.333 --> 35:58.417
Same as you can't take
eggs out of a soufflé.

35:58.500 --> 36:01.083
- Well, it's only a metaphor.
- Only a metaphor!

36:01.166 --> 36:03.125
- Patrick--
- But it doesn't work!

36:03.208 --> 36:05.333
Could we move on? Please?

36:11.959 --> 36:13.917
[chatter]

36:19.083 --> 36:20.083
Becky.

36:20.166 --> 36:21.291
Self-harming,
resistant depressive.

36:23.000 --> 36:23.959
Patrick.

36:24.041 --> 36:25.291
Narcissistic, schizoid,
suicidal alcoholic.

36:27.500 --> 36:29.834
How many types of medication
do they have you on?

36:29.917 --> 36:32.250
Three. Two anti-depressants
and a tranquillizer.

36:33.166 --> 36:35.917
- I'm on eight.
- Then I suppose you win.

36:36.000 --> 36:38.041
[laughs]

36:46.291 --> 36:50.041
I think a lot of my relationship
problems stem from the fact

36:50.125 --> 36:52.125
that the person
I'm having a relationship with

36:52.208 --> 36:55.125
doesn't know
we're in a relationship.

36:55.208 --> 36:57.458
[laughing] Fuck, Jill!

36:57.542 --> 36:59.625
No wonder you're here
for the ninth time!

36:59.709 --> 37:01.458
[stifles a sob]

37:02.750 --> 37:04.917
[Jill sobs]

37:05.959 --> 37:07.875
You're going to have to
apologize for that.

37:07.959 --> 37:09.083
Why? I meant it.

37:09.166 --> 37:12.291
That's why
you have to apologize.

37:12.375 --> 37:15.333
But I wouldn't mean it
if I apologized.

37:15.417 --> 37:19.583
Fake it to make it, man.
Fake it to make it.

37:21.125 --> 37:23.083
Fuck!

37:39.041 --> 37:40.500
Patrick!

37:43.083 --> 37:45.166
I was looking for you.

37:45.250 --> 37:46.917
- They're throwing me out.
- Really?

37:47.000 --> 37:48.917
They say I'm a...
disruptive influence.

37:49.000 --> 37:51.333
I don't contribute.

37:51.417 --> 37:54.291
Of course I don't fucking
contribute, I'm depressed!

37:54.375 --> 37:57.083
Fuck, I hate this fucking place!

37:57.166 --> 37:59.792
- Rebecca...
- I can't go back to my parents.

38:00.500 --> 38:03.000
This is my sister's address.

38:03.083 --> 38:05.875
She's away, so...
I'll be there alone.

38:07.041 --> 38:09.000
[Gordon]
Miss Owen, now, please.

38:09.083 --> 38:11.417
Come and find me.

38:28.125 --> 38:30.333
[low conversations]

38:37.417 --> 38:38.875
[low conversations]

38:38.959 --> 38:41.500
♪ ♪

39:05.125 --> 39:07.709
Well done. You came back.

39:09.166 --> 39:10.333
Oh, I still want to leave.

39:10.417 --> 39:13.083
I want to leave with
that waitress over there.

39:13.166 --> 39:15.166
Christ, look at her.

39:15.250 --> 39:17.667
Do you think if I told her
it was my mother's funeral

39:17.750 --> 39:18.917
and I needed cheering up--

39:19.000 --> 39:21.333
She might be
the one to save you?

39:22.834 --> 39:24.583
It's worth a try.

39:26.500 --> 39:30.709
Patrick, it turns out
Fleur is an old friend

39:30.792 --> 39:32.750
- of your mother's.
- Yes, actually,
we've met before.

39:32.834 --> 39:35.625
- Your mother saved my life.
- Really?

39:35.709 --> 39:39.792
She gave me a job in one of
the charity shops she ran.

39:39.875 --> 39:42.375
And that is where I had
one of my episodes.

39:42.458 --> 39:45.875
We'd had a fur coat in
that morning.

39:45.959 --> 39:48.125
It was an amazing sable coat.

39:48.208 --> 39:51.291
And I put it on,
emptied the till, shut the shop,

39:51.375 --> 39:54.041
hailed a cab and I said,
"Take me to The Ritz!"

39:54.125 --> 39:57.625
And I sat in the Palm Court
drinking champagne cocktails

39:57.709 --> 39:59.959
and talking to anyone
who would listen.

40:00.041 --> 40:03.166
And eventually the police
were summoned,

40:03.250 --> 40:05.875
and I had no one to
call on but your mother.

40:05.959 --> 40:07.959
And I promised
I'd never do it again.

40:08.041 --> 40:09.166
I mean, I did.

40:09.250 --> 40:11.166
Many, many times.

40:11.250 --> 40:14.291
But you should be
very proud of her.

40:14.375 --> 40:17.667
She did an enormous amount
of practical good.

40:17.750 --> 40:20.125
And she's touched
hundreds of lives.

40:20.208 --> 40:22.041
Very good of you to let me know.
Thank you.

40:22.125 --> 40:25.000
- So... Do you?
- Do I what?

40:25.083 --> 40:28.291
Do you feel proud
of your mother?

40:29.250 --> 40:34.458
- I'm really not sure.
- You're not sure?

40:34.542 --> 40:36.083
Well, you're worse
than my children.

40:36.166 --> 40:40.041
- Sorry,
I really ought to circulate.
- Absolute bastards.

40:40.959 --> 40:42.125
All of you...

40:43.458 --> 40:46.834
So what did
the lunatic have to say?

40:46.917 --> 40:49.000
She suggested
there's no easy conclusion

40:49.083 --> 40:51.333
about what
someone's life means.

40:51.417 --> 40:54.917
You can come to a conclusion
about what it means to you.

40:56.083 --> 40:59.291
Actually, I feel inconclusive
about both my parents.

41:00.458 --> 41:01.500
Sounds exhausting.

41:01.583 --> 41:04.208
Isn't it easier
just to loathe their guts?

41:04.291 --> 41:06.041
Yes, I tried that
with my father.

41:06.125 --> 41:08.166
No good.

41:08.250 --> 41:09.375
The truth is I feel everything:

41:09.458 --> 41:14.291
contempt, pity, rage, terror...

41:14.792 --> 41:16.875
and tenderness.

41:16.959 --> 41:18.083
Tenderness?

41:18.166 --> 41:23.041
At the thought of how
unhappy he was, they both were.

41:23.125 --> 41:27.959
And then of course I remember
I have sons of my own
and the loathing floods back.

41:29.834 --> 41:33.834
Well, I hate bereavement.
It plays havoc
with your eyeliner.

41:33.917 --> 41:35.875
I didn't realize
my mother meant so much.

41:35.959 --> 41:37.834
Oh, it's nothing to do with her.

41:37.917 --> 41:39.834
It's just the way
tears spring on you,

41:39.917 --> 41:42.500
at a funeral or a silly film.

41:42.583 --> 41:44.542
Not brought on by the thing
that triggers them,

41:44.625 --> 41:50.041
just from a generalized sadness,
I suppose.

41:50.125 --> 41:53.458
Sometimes the trigger and
the sadness are the same thing.

41:55.291 --> 41:57.542
Occasionally.

42:00.000 --> 42:00.959
Oh, Christ,
I wonder what it'd be like

42:01.041 --> 42:02.583
to have an unconditioned
response about something,

42:02.667 --> 42:05.917
anything,
without irony and detachment,

42:06.000 --> 42:09.333
just to be spontaneous,
to feel something--

42:09.417 --> 42:11.125
Well, it's no use asking me.

42:13.000 --> 42:15.750
No.

42:15.834 --> 42:18.125
Sorry, erm... you can't
actually smoke out here.

42:19.458 --> 42:21.542
Really? I didn't know.

42:24.458 --> 42:27.125
It's funny,
because it is outside.

42:27.208 --> 42:29.041
It's technically
still part of the club,

42:29.125 --> 42:31.458
and er...there's no smoking
anywhere in the club.

42:31.542 --> 42:32.875
So...

42:32.959 --> 42:34.875
Well,
I'd better put it out, then.

43:00.125 --> 43:02.208
Er... No, let me.

43:05.166 --> 43:06.542
- I'm so sorry about that.
- It's okay.

43:06.625 --> 43:08.625
I'm used to it.

43:13.625 --> 43:15.583
[sighs]

43:18.458 --> 43:20.500
♪ ♪

43:27.208 --> 43:28.166
Excuse me? Hello. Sorry.

43:28.250 --> 43:31.333
Er... I just...
I wondered if I could erm...

43:31.417 --> 43:33.375
Tea or coffee?

43:33.458 --> 43:35.667
Actually, no,
it's something else.

43:35.750 --> 43:38.208
Erm...

43:38.291 --> 43:42.375
I just... Would you mind...
if I took your number?

43:43.375 --> 43:45.500
[electricity softly fizzing]

43:47.583 --> 43:50.333
[inhales and exhales heavily]

44:11.083 --> 44:13.333
[snorts]

44:16.083 --> 44:18.417
- Oh, Christ.
- Hello.

44:19.125 --> 44:21.542
- Are you leaving?
- Sssh.

44:21.625 --> 44:23.959
Oh, I must say,
I don't envy you.

44:24.041 --> 44:27.375
I love it here. It gets me away
from my awful children.

44:27.458 --> 44:30.583
The little shits. I loathe them.

44:30.667 --> 44:32.375
Do you have children yourself?

44:32.458 --> 44:34.375
Actually, I'm sorry,
I'm trying to...

44:34.458 --> 44:36.166
Well, if I have one word
of advice, it's this.

44:36.250 --> 44:38.583
Amitriptyline.

44:38.667 --> 44:39.750
The only time I've ever
been happy was on it,

44:39.834 --> 44:41.834
but these bastards
won't give me any.

44:41.917 --> 44:44.959
The thing is, I'm trying
not to take anything, so...

44:45.041 --> 44:48.625
Don't be ridiculous.
It's the most marvelous drug.

44:48.709 --> 44:50.083
Amitriptyline!

44:54.333 --> 44:56.583
- [low chatter]
- [waitress laughs]

44:56.667 --> 45:01.625
I'd expected more people.
She was very well-loved.

45:01.709 --> 45:05.083
Well, she lost touch with people
when she stopped speaking.

45:05.166 --> 45:06.041
It must have been
terrible for her,

45:06.125 --> 45:09.166
not to be able to say
what she wanted to,

45:09.250 --> 45:10.917
especially to Patrick.

45:11.000 --> 45:13.125
That's why we must all resolve
to drop our defenses

45:13.208 --> 45:15.500
and say what we feel,
while we can.

45:15.583 --> 45:18.667
- Mummy!
- And then at this point
the English usually say,

45:18.750 --> 45:22.125
"Well, this is
a cheerful subject!"

45:22.208 --> 45:24.250
I see you two
are still glued to each other.

45:24.333 --> 45:27.291
Well, no one can hope
to ignore their children
as completely as you did.

45:28.333 --> 45:30.291
Mary!

45:30.375 --> 45:32.542
You go and find Robert, darling.

45:32.625 --> 45:35.125
We always communicated!

45:35.208 --> 45:37.125
Do you remember
what you said to me

45:37.208 --> 45:40.458
when you telephoned me at
school to say Daddy had died?

45:40.542 --> 45:44.417
- Well, I said how awful it was.
- "Cheer up," you said.

45:44.500 --> 45:46.291
"Cheer up"! You never had
any idea who I was then

45:46.375 --> 45:48.542
and you still don't now.

45:53.208 --> 45:55.041
How are you, dear?

45:56.583 --> 45:58.166
Well...

45:58.250 --> 46:00.834
considering I've just had my
head bitten off by my daughter.

46:00.917 --> 46:03.417
Has she had
mental health problems?

46:04.417 --> 46:06.959
I beg your pardon?

46:13.917 --> 46:17.166
Have you had
mental health problems?

46:21.583 --> 46:23.750
Have we met?

46:23.834 --> 46:26.417
Well, I just have a feeling
for these things.

46:27.291 --> 46:28.917
So, have you?

46:29.000 --> 46:33.125
No, I have not had
"mental health problems".

46:33.208 --> 46:38.291
Even in this degenerate age
of confession and complaint,

46:38.375 --> 46:41.375
when the vocabulary
of Freudian mumbo-jumbo

46:41.458 --> 46:43.250
is emptied onto
every conversation

46:43.333 --> 46:46.709
like vinegar onto a newspaper
full of sodden chips,

46:46.792 --> 46:48.542
some of us choose
not to tuck in!

46:48.625 --> 46:51.375
As if it weren't
ludicrous enough

46:51.458 --> 46:53.417
that every child must be gifted,

46:53.500 --> 46:56.250
they now have to be
ill as well.

46:56.333 --> 46:59.750
A touch of Asperger's,
some autism,

46:59.834 --> 47:01.375
dyslexia stalks
the playground!

47:01.458 --> 47:03.417
Poor little things.

47:03.500 --> 47:04.709
If they can't confess
to being abused,

47:04.792 --> 47:08.750
they must confess
to being abusive!

47:08.834 --> 47:09.875
Well, my dear -

47:09.959 --> 47:12.709
I call you my dear
from what is no doubt known as

47:12.792 --> 47:15.583
- "Sincerity Deficit Disorder" -
- [chuckles]

47:15.667 --> 47:19.208
no, I have never suffered
the slightest taint
of mental illness

47:19.291 --> 47:20.667
because I am
the impossible man -

47:20.750 --> 47:23.792
the man who is entirely well!

47:23.875 --> 47:26.667
- Psychotherapists scatter...
- You are completely
off your rocker!

47:26.750 --> 47:28.917
- And I thought as much...
- ..in my presence, ashamed
of their sham profession.

47:29.000 --> 47:32.208
- ..my little radar.
- Bugger off!

47:32.291 --> 47:34.917
A month in the clinic will
do you the power of good

47:35.000 --> 47:37.458
because it will re-clothe you
in your rightful mind.

47:37.542 --> 47:39.166
♪ Oh, the Father of Mankind ♪

47:39.250 --> 47:40.959
♪ Forgive our foolish ways ♪
- Is everything alright?

47:41.041 --> 47:44.583
Oh, God, here he is!

47:44.667 --> 47:47.542
Like an exhibit
in a courtroom drama.

47:47.625 --> 47:50.291
- A practicing witch doctor.
- I was just trying
to help this poor man...

47:50.375 --> 47:53.709
- A man happy to turn my
daughter against her own father.
- ..of mental health problems.

47:53.792 --> 47:56.250
Inventing repulsive fantasies,

47:56.333 --> 48:00.875
polluting human imagination
with murderous babies

48:00.959 --> 48:02.041
and incestuous...

48:03.542 --> 48:05.500
[glass shatters]

48:06.834 --> 48:09.125
- [clattering]
- [cries of shock]

48:09.208 --> 48:12.250
[Fleur] Well, he has got himself
all worked up.

48:12.333 --> 48:15.458
- I'll call an ambulance.
[Fleur] Hoist with his own
petard.

48:15.542 --> 48:16.792
As they say.

48:16.875 --> 48:18.458
Oh, God,
that would really finish me off.

48:18.542 --> 48:20.583
Is she praying?

48:20.667 --> 48:23.458
[Robert] That's nice of her.
- ..return to the mother...

48:24.333 --> 48:27.625
[Annette continues
reciting prayer]

48:27.709 --> 48:29.125
[Patrick] Johnny.

48:31.709 --> 48:33.667
[Julia] Say goodbye
to your father for me.

48:38.625 --> 48:41.625
Pat... Pat...

48:43.542 --> 48:46.250
Pat...

48:48.792 --> 48:50.417
Pat... Pat...

48:50.500 --> 48:52.917
Pat...

48:54.125 --> 48:55.667
[shallow breaths]

48:55.750 --> 48:58.583
♪ ominous music ♪

49:19.667 --> 49:21.583
Heart attack, apparently.

49:21.667 --> 49:22.834
You can tell by the cold nose.

49:22.917 --> 49:25.417
I'll go with him
to the hospital.

49:26.750 --> 49:29.291
What an emotional day!

49:31.959 --> 49:34.709
Don't worry, Nick,
I won't leave your side.

49:37.959 --> 49:40.750
I must go.
I've a patient at four.

49:40.834 --> 49:43.667
- Thank you.
- Well done.

49:43.750 --> 49:45.417
For what?
The public breakdown?

49:45.500 --> 49:47.041
In the trade it's what
we'd call a breakthrough.

49:47.125 --> 49:51.375
Yes, well...
without getting Californian...

49:52.709 --> 49:54.375
..I'm grateful.

49:54.834 --> 49:57.417
[siren wails]

50:00.917 --> 50:03.375
Are you coming back with us?

50:05.500 --> 50:08.417
You'd be very welcome.

50:08.500 --> 50:11.041
No, I'll see you at the weekend.
Come here.

50:12.500 --> 50:14.083
- See you at the weekend.
- You could...

50:14.166 --> 50:15.166
just come back and have
some dinner, just us four.

50:15.250 --> 50:17.875
- Very quiet.
- No, I think I'll crash out.

50:17.959 --> 50:20.834
'Cause it's been a long day.

50:21.542 --> 50:24.792
Well, if you change your mind...

50:25.667 --> 50:26.458
Thank you.

50:26.542 --> 50:29.083
In fact,
you should change your mind.

50:30.125 --> 50:31.250
That's what it's for.

50:41.750 --> 50:43.542
[exhales]

50:49.750 --> 50:51.750
[inhales deeply]

50:53.875 --> 50:55.917
[exhales deeply]

50:57.625 --> 50:59.625
"And now I keep thinking
I'm a moth!"

50:59.709 --> 51:01.792
"Very interesting,"
says the psychiatrist.

51:01.875 --> 51:03.208
"What made you come here today?"

51:03.291 --> 51:06.750
"Well," he says, "I saw
the light in the window."

51:08.041 --> 51:08.917
Very good.

51:09.000 --> 51:11.500
Do you specialize in these jobs

51:11.583 --> 51:13.750
because of your
sunny disposition?

51:13.834 --> 51:17.041
You say that,
but last year, for four months,

51:17.125 --> 51:19.000
I literally
couldn't get out of bed.

51:20.041 --> 51:22.625
- Couldn't see the point.
- Oh.

51:25.166 --> 51:27.709
Oh, well, I'm...
sorry to hear that.

51:40.250 --> 51:43.625
Believe me, Mr. Melrose,
in a month's time

51:43.709 --> 51:45.000
you'll look back and think,

51:45.083 --> 51:47.583
"What was all the fuss about?
What was I thinking?"

51:47.667 --> 51:50.333
That's what happened to me,
anyway. Is this it, then?

51:53.166 --> 51:56.083
Very nice. They'll be pleased
to get their dad back.

51:56.834 --> 51:59.875
- Who?
- The kids.

52:00.875 --> 52:02.500
Good luck with it, mate.

52:16.917 --> 52:19.709
Actually, I know this
might sound a bit crazy -

52:19.792 --> 52:21.750
for want of a better word -
but could you take me back?

52:21.834 --> 52:23.834
To the hospital?

52:24.583 --> 52:26.458
I don't think I'm quite ready.

52:30.125 --> 52:32.417
Fuckin' hell...you people.

52:37.125 --> 52:40.208
[man] Fear knocked on the door.

52:40.959 --> 52:43.250
Courage opened the door.

52:46.000 --> 52:47.333
And there was nobody there!

52:53.250 --> 52:54.583
Please, carry on.

52:58.875 --> 53:00.667
[grunts]

53:15.667 --> 53:16.792
Bravo.

53:19.166 --> 53:21.166
[chuckles]

53:23.917 --> 53:26.208
[phone rings]

53:29.333 --> 53:33.583
- [phone continues ringing]
- Come on, come on.

53:37.041 --> 53:38.000
- Hello?
[Annette] Patrick?

53:38.083 --> 53:40.917
Hello? Patrick, is that you?

53:41.000 --> 53:42.959
- Yes.
- Annette here.

53:43.041 --> 53:43.917
I'm afraid
I've rather bad news.

53:44.000 --> 53:46.250
Nicholas didn't make it.

53:46.333 --> 53:48.500
- He stopped breathing
in the ambulance.
- [exhales heavily]

53:49.333 --> 53:50.083
Oh, Patrick, are you crying?

53:50.166 --> 53:52.750
No, no,
I'm just out of breath.

53:52.834 --> 53:55.166
Though, of course,
I'm also very sad.

53:55.250 --> 53:57.291
Amazing man,
completely unique.

53:57.375 --> 53:59.375
Let's hope so.
The idea of a whole village

53:59.458 --> 54:02.625
full of Nicholas Pratts
is rather terrifying.

54:07.291 --> 54:08.875
Patrick?

54:08.959 --> 54:10.542
I'm sorry, it's only
just occurred to me.

54:10.625 --> 54:13.750
He was the... the last one.

54:13.834 --> 54:15.750
Last of my parents' circle.

54:16.417 --> 54:18.000
They're all gone now.

54:18.083 --> 54:20.625
Oh, now you're making me cry.

54:20.709 --> 54:21.667
Oh, really, there's no need.

54:21.750 --> 54:23.333
Thank you for what
you said at the funeral too.

54:23.417 --> 54:26.250
It was helpful
to have another point of view.

54:26.333 --> 54:28.041
She might not have been
the perfect mother.

54:28.125 --> 54:29.166
That must anger you.

54:29.250 --> 54:32.667
But sometimes those
who deserve the most blame

54:32.750 --> 54:35.667
also deserve
the most compassion.

54:35.750 --> 54:37.500
Goodbye, Patrick.

54:45.250 --> 54:47.291
[receiver slams on cradle]

54:49.834 --> 54:52.667
[exhales heavily]

54:59.125 --> 55:01.208
[David] Patrick?

55:03.166 --> 55:06.083
♪ ominous music ♪

55:13.041 --> 55:16.625
[breathing heavily]

55:16.709 --> 55:18.583
Patrick, where are you?

55:21.792 --> 55:23.750
[exhales heavily]

55:37.083 --> 55:39.041
Helene.

55:43.500 --> 55:45.583
[keys in number]

55:46.041 --> 55:48.875
[ringing tone]

55:49.834 --> 55:51.709
Hello?

55:51.792 --> 55:54.750
Oh, hello, it's Patrick here.

55:54.834 --> 55:56.917
Hello.

55:57.000 --> 55:59.792
I've decided
I'm bored of ghosts.

55:59.875 --> 56:01.834
I want to see people instead.

56:02.417 --> 56:05.917
I see. Okay...

56:06.000 --> 56:09.083
Well, is it too late
to change my mind?

56:09.166 --> 56:11.208
[Mary] Not at all.

56:11.291 --> 56:13.834
After all...
that's what it's for.

56:13.917 --> 56:15.875
[chuckles]

56:15.959 --> 56:18.291
The boys
will be delighted to see you.

56:25.166 --> 56:27.959
[receiver clicks on cradle]

56:30.333 --> 56:32.291
[exhales]

56:37.000 --> 56:39.458
[thud]

56:39.542 --> 56:41.583
♪ ominous music ♪

56:45.709 --> 56:47.417
[Patrick] I'm going
to the bathroom.

56:50.041 --> 56:52.792
Well, don't be long.

56:58.125 --> 57:00.041
[door creaks shut]

57:05.834 --> 57:07.667
[breathing heavily]

57:09.041 --> 57:10.125
Patrick?

57:15.583 --> 57:17.750
Patrick, where are you?

57:20.500 --> 57:21.709
[shouts] Patrick!

57:39.166 --> 57:41.792
Come and sit here.

57:44.208 --> 57:45.709
No.

57:52.291 --> 57:53.583
- Beg pardon?
- No.

57:54.417 --> 57:57.083
I won't do what you say anymore.

58:00.000 --> 58:04.709
Patrick. Don't talk like that
to your dear old dad.

58:04.792 --> 58:06.417
It's wrong.
You're wrong!

58:06.500 --> 58:09.792
Nobody should do that
to anybody else.

58:24.000 --> 58:26.667
[grunts]

58:36.083 --> 58:38.583
Right.

58:46.959 --> 58:48.917
Yeah. [mutters]

59:03.041 --> 59:04.709
[breathing deeply]

59:14.333 --> 59:16.041
[dull roar of traffic outside]

59:26.041 --> 59:28.000
[Blur] "Tender"

1:00:11.375 --> 1:00:14.583
♪ Tender is the night ♪

1:00:14.667 --> 1:00:18.041
♪ Lying by your side ♪

1:00:18.125 --> 1:00:21.208
♪ Tender is the touch ♪

1:00:21.291 --> 1:00:24.625
♪ Of someone that
you love too much ♪

1:00:24.709 --> 1:00:27.333
♪ Tender is the day ♪

1:00:27.417 --> 1:00:31.208
♪ The demons go away ♪

1:00:31.291 --> 1:00:33.500
♪ Lord I need to find ♪

1:00:33.583 --> 1:00:38.250
♪ Someone who can
heal my mind ♪

1:00:38.333 --> 1:00:42.041
♪ Come on, come on, come on ♪

1:00:42.125 --> 1:00:44.542
♪ Get through it ♪

1:00:44.625 --> 1:00:48.417
♪ Come on, come on, come on ♪

1:00:48.500 --> 1:00:51.125
♪ Love's the greatest thing ♪

1:00:51.208 --> 1:00:54.375
♪ Come on ♪
